    "This comparative analysis is crucial in understanding the strengths and limitations of each method in predicting WCET for real-time robotic systems.To validate the effectiveness of this method, we conducted two industrial case studies, including the implementation of collision detection algorithms; and the control of a robot with 6-DOF.",
    "These case studies were chosen to illustrate the applicability of our computational methods to real-world scenarios.",
    "Through these practical applications, we examined the potential of our method to enhance WCET estimations in complex and dynamic environments.",
    "The results from these studies [19] provide insights into how our method can be utilized to address the challenges inherent in modern real-time systems, showcasing its versatility and robustness.",
    "ContributionsThis thesis makes the following contributions:• Focus on Robotic Systems: Unlike previous studies that primarily concentrate on embedded systems, this research specifically targets robotic systems."
